      { q: 'What disinfectant kills the flu virus?', a: 'Use an EPA-registered disinfectant that lists influenza on its label. Check EPA List N for verified products. The disinfectant must remain wet on the surface for the full contact time specified on the label to achieve its kill claims.' },
      { q: 'Can enhanced cleaning really reduce workplace flu cases?', a: 'Yes. Organizations that implement comprehensive flu season cleaning programs report 20 to 50 percent reductions in flu-related absenteeism. The key is consistent execution of high-touch disinfection, proper product selection, and complementary measures like hand hygiene infrastructure.' }
